        "requester-9@example.invalid", "x_casemgmt_demo_agent",
        "x_casemgmt_demo_team") do not include any PII tokens.
      - Choice-value validation: <type>Complaint</type>,
        <status>Resolved</status>, <priority>High</priority> -
        capital C, capital R, capital H respectively.
      - Anti-pattern validation: NO <number>, NO <opened_date>,
        NO <closed_date>, NO <pending_reason> elements present.
      - Sys-id-literal validation: only ONE <sys_id> element (the
        case's own primary key); NO sys_id literals appear in any
        cross-reference field.
      - Scope-identifier validation: the concrete scope identifier `casemgmt` is used verbatim in the sys_class_name, sys_update_name,
        all reference values, and the file path; ServiceNow Update Set imports use a standard XML parser, so the scope id is concrete in the XML before export. The same identifier is used consistently across every cross-reference in this file.

    Key insights (per the agent prompt):
      1. Demo case 09 is the canonical Resolved Complaint case; the
         Complaint-flow analog of demo case 05 (Resolved General
         Inquiry).
      2. THIS CASE IS THE COMPLAINT-FLOW RESOLVE-SUCCESS TEST. Both
         flows (general_inquiry and complaint) MUST behave identically
         when all child tasks are Closed.
      3. The closed_date field is intentionally empty even though this
         case is Resolved - the set_closed_date business rule fires
         only on Resolved -> Closed update.
      4. Demo case 09 has one Closed task per the seed script; with
         this single Closed task and ZERO non-Closed tasks, the
         validate_resolved_transition subflow allows the transition.
      5. Demo case 09 has one Person-type party (the demo agent as
         Witness role). This exercises the polymorphic UI Policy on
         the Person side for the Complaint flow.
      6. The case populates the Resolved slice/bar of the
         case_count_by_status donut and all_cases_by_status bar.
      7. The case does NOT appear in the Agent Workspace's "My Open
         Cases" list (filter excludes Resolved and Closed).
      8. The complaint and general_inquiry flows MUST be functionally
         identical per AAP Section 0.5.5; this case validates the
         complaint flow's resolve-success path.
      9. High priority is appropriate for a Complaint at Resolved
         status; contrasts naturally with case 08 (In Progress
         Complaint at Critical) where the priority drops as the
         urgency decreases through the lifecycle.
-->
